wiki.content: I think this is a good song because it had good words and it inspires people! 💦 American singer, songwriter, rapper, dancer and actor Chris Brown's “Don't Wake Me Up” peaked at No.2 in the UK charts earlier this year – the track is taken from his fifth studio album “Fortune”. Everyone's shouting out "Auto-Tue" left and right as if they're exposing something sacred. Um, you all aren't... you all are stating the obvious. We know this has auto-tune! These days, it's used for more than just pitch correction. It's used literally as an effect... an over-layer to add to the digital and electronic aesthetics of modern pop music. Also, he hit a girl... NEXT! I'm not saying that it's okay and everyone needs to forget about it. What I am saying is that if it affects your listening experience, then simply don't listen. All you're doing is continuing the negativity. I'm sure he doesn't want to hear about it the rest of his life and neither does the victim. So keep it to yourself.
